* System & Performance

** Directory Cleanup (~no-littering~)

The ~no-littering~ package automatically redirects temporary and state files 
created by Emacs and its packages to the ~var/~ and ~etc/~ subdirectories inside =~/.emacs.d/=.

#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  (use-package no-littering
    :ensure t
    :demand t
    :config
    ;; Redirect auto-save files (#filename#) to var/auto-save/
    (setq auto-save-file-name-transforms
          `((".*" ,(no-littering-expand-var-file-name "auto-save/") t)))

    ;; Redirect backup files (filename~) to var/backup/
    (setq backup-directory-alist
          `((".*" . ,(no-littering-expand-var-file-name "backup/")))))
#+end_src


* System Settings & Native Options (~emacs-native~)

** Minimalist Interface & UI
Disable unnecessary UI elements and configure cursor and search scrolling behavior.

#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  ;; Hide UI elements
  (tool-bar-mode -1)
  (menu-bar-mode -1)
  (scroll-bar-mode -1)
  (global-display-line-numbers-mode -1)

  ;; Editing and navigation behavior
  (delete-selection-mode 1)                         ; Replace selected text when typing
  (setq isearch-allow-scroll 'unlimited)            ; Allow scrolling during isearch
  (setq help-window-select t)                       ; Automatically focus *Help* windows
  (setq-default cursor-in-non-selected-windows nil) ; Hide cursor in inactive windows
#+end_src

