** Help Window Management (~quit-window~)
Ensure pressing ~q~ in help buffers completely kills the buffer instead of just burying it.
/Note: Uses ~define-advice~, the modern replacement for ~defadvice~./

#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  (define-advice quit-window (:before (&optional kill window) always-kill)
    "Ensure `quit-window' always kills the buffer when called interactively."
    (when (called-interactively-p 'interactive)
      (setq kill t)))
#+end_src


