* Editing & Completion Tools

** In-Buffer Completion (~company~)

Provides modern text and code auto-completion. Uses ~M-j~/~M-k~ for navigation 
and ~TAB~ to insert the selection, leaving ~RET~ strictly for newlines.

#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  (use-package company
    :ensure t
    :defer t
    :hook ((prog-mode . company-mode)
           (geiser-repl-mode . company-mode))
    :custom
    (company-minimum-prefix-length 1)
    (company-idle-delay 0.0)
    (company-selection-wrap-around t)
    (company-tooltip-align-annotations t)
    :bind
    (("C-SPC" . company-complete)
     :map company-active-map
     ("M-j" . company-select-next)
     ("M-k" . company-select-previous)
     ("<tab>" . company-complete-selection)
     ("TAB" . company-complete-selection)
     ("<enter>" . nil)
     ("RET" . nil)
     ("C-h" . nil)))
#+end_src

** Smart Parentheses (~smartparens~)

Automatic insertion, structural editing, and strict pairing for code and notes.
Disables apostrophe auto-pairing to prevent issues with Lisp quote notation (~'~).

#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  (use-package smartparens
    :ensure t
    :hook (((prog-mode geiser-repl-mode org-mode) . smartparens-mode)
           ((prog-mode geiser-repl-mode) . smartparens-strict-mode))
    :config
    (require 'smartparens-config)
    ;; Disable quote auto-pairing for Lisp friendliness
    (sp-pair "'" nil :actions nil)
    ;; Disable overlay highlights
    (setq sp-highlight-pair-overlay nil)
    (setq sp-highlight-wrap-overlay nil)
    (setq sp-highlight-wrap-tag-overlay nil))
#+end_src

