* Org Mode Environment

** Core Org Settings & Babel Execution (~org~)

Configures Org Mode with Babel language evaluation (Python, JS, Graphviz Dot, Racket), 
disables evaluation confirmation prompts, and sets keybindings for inserting code blocks.

#+begin_src emacs-lisp
  (use-package org
    :ensure nil
    :hook (org-mode . visual-line-mode)
    :bind (:map org-mode-map
                ("s-i" . (lambda () (interactive) (insert "#+begin_src \n#+end_src") (forward-line -1) (end-of-line))))
    :custom
    ;; Babel execution settings
    (org-confirm-babel-evaluate nil)
    (org-edit-src-content-indentation 0)
    
    :config
    ;; Load Org Babel languages
    (org-babel-do-load-languages
     'org-babel-load-languages
     '((python . t)
       (js . t)
       (racket . t))))
#+end_src

